cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.DS 

This paper deals with packet sampling in the Internet to infer flow statistics. The most relevant sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses heuristics based on measurements from different backbone IP networks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and rescaling, which could be related to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
